overview: The user wanted to transform their sleep questionnaire app from a
  generic design to a beautiful, professional, and calming experience. I began
  by analyzing the existing codebase to identify aesthetic shortcomings, then
  implemented a new sleep-themed color palette, custom gradients, and refined
  component styling. The main form layout was redesigned with subtle background
  elements and an improved progress indicator. All questionnaire sections,
  including the intro and report, received consistent thematic updates,
  replacing generic gray boxes and inconsistent colors with cohesive, branded
  styles. Along the way, a React console error related to null input values was
  identified and fixed by safely handling values in the  component.
  Further refinements were made to alert styling and section border opacity
  based on user feedback, ensuring a polished and unified visual language
  throughout the application.
